  "experiment": "02-computed-style-diff",
  "method": "Vite serves React canonical (@cloudflare/kumo subpath exports) and the native generated svelte components under one page sharing kumo-standalone.css. Headless 'Google Chrome for Testing' is driven over CDP (Node global WebSocket, no Playwright/puppeteer dep). For each component the harness walks every element in the React subtree and the native subtree, records getComputedStyle for ~30 box/color/border props, aligns the two trees via an LCS over (depth:tag) signatures, then reports per-pair style deltas plus elements present in React but MISSING in native.",
