  "notes": [
    "getComputedStyle diff pinpoints WRONG values (spacing/size/background/color) precisely, with numeric before/after.",
    "BLUNT on the checkbox 'wrong padding': there is NO literal padding delta (both boxes are padding:0). The real native spacing defect surfaces as marginTop 2px->0px (React mt-0.5 vs native 0), align-items flex-start->center on the label, and a box width/height delta. A gate keyed only on 'padding' would MISS it; keying on the padding+margin+alignment+size family catches it.",
    "MISSING structural elements (checkbox checkmark svg) are only caught because the LCS alignment leaves them unmatched -> a pure per-pair style diff alone would MISS them; the 'missing_in_native' list is doing that work (overlaps with E03 dom-structure-diff).",
    "Switch 'missing track' shows up as a backgroundColor delta (React checked track bg-blue-500 vs native transparent) and a width/height delta (React h-4.5 w-9 vs native h-4 w-8), not as a missing element.",
    "Requires the SAME stylesheet + a real layout engine; deterministic (no AA/font sampling like pixel-diff). Per-component cost = one mount pair; fast.",
    "Weakness: alignment is heuristic. Deeply restructured trees can misalign and inflate deltas; needs role/testid anchors for complex components."
  ],
